=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Mono-protect 2-methylhydroquinone (2-methylbenzene-1,4-diol) as the benzyl ether (BnBr, base) to give 4-benzyloxy-2-methylphenol | Step 2: O-alkylate the free phenol with ethyl bromoacetate/K2CO3 to form ethyl 2-(4-benzyloxy-2-methylphenoxy)acetate | Step 3: Hydrogenolysis (H2, Pd/C) removes Bn to give ethyl 2-(4-hydroxy-2-methylphenoxy)acetate | Step 4: Couple this phenol with tert-butyl 3-bromobenzoate under Ullmann/Buchwald diaryl-ether conditions (e.g., CuI or Pd catalyst, base) to obtain tert-butyl 3-(4-(2-ethoxy-2-oxoethoxy)-2-methylphenoxy)benzoate | Step 5: Remove the tert-butyl ester with TFA to give 3-(4-(2-ethoxy-2-oxoethoxy)-2-methylphenoxy)benzoic acid | Step 6: Convert the acid to the acid chloride with SOCl2 (or oxalyl chloride/DMF) to reach CCOC(=O)COc1ccc(Oc2cccc(C(=O)Cl)c2)cc1C.

